<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
AHAHAHA!  I have some questions that ought to really put Verant on the spot.<P>Why hasn't the group bug which makes it impossible to invite a player until he relogs been fixed yet?  When is it going to be fixed?  Why has this bug been left standing nearly 9 months since game release?  Do you have a specific person assigned to this bug? (I bet i could track this bug down in 10 minutes)<P>How long are you going to leave he/she string in emotes uninitialized?<P>What is the reasoning behind having players click through 5 or 6 different splash screens to get into the actual game?<P>Why don't your programmers set the edit control of the patch window so that it displays the top of the patch message and not the bottom of it?  Is this beyond their realm of expertise?<P>Why only 12 social slots for 36 hotkeys?  Has it occurred to Verant that this number is sorely inadequate?<P>Why do socials act as 5 separate and very, very short commands, instead of what would be the obvious behavior (a nice long command line)?<P>Does it seem reasonable to bind such common actions as sitting to a keyboard key?  Most of the keyboard is sitting unused and the player is forced to rely on a sorely deficient hotkey system.<P>Why do you post network information and messages after the login process (which is, by definition, affected by your network and thus a stupid place to be putting network status information).<P>Please explain how broken quests get by your QA process.  Please also explain how the Summon Corpse spell bug got by your QA.  Testing these things is so trivial that these additions could not possibly have been tested even ONCE before a patch.  What steps is Verant taking to prevent such things from happening again?<P>What sort of gameplay purpose do NO RENT items serve (with the exception of summoned items)?  Specifically, I fail to see how a 500 plat NO RENT key can be justified as anything but a device to waste player time when he accidentally goes linkdead or when you shutdown your servers without notice.<P>Why have you combined the chat and login servers into a single and very prone point of failure?  What's the ETA on Verant doing this the correct way?  (Everyone knows this problem by now, so i won't bother explaining it).<P>You can, of course, leave the snide remarks out, but I'm gonna have a laugh at their responses to any of these questions.
