A few questions:<P>Why does a bard have to hit 2 keys to switch to a new song, 1 to stop and 1 to start a song.  Worst of all there is a graphics portion of the ungraying of the key so that people with slow computers take longer to start a new song than people with fast computers.<P>Will they up the number of key component items on the mobs so that we wont be forced to commit suicide in mass, buy coffins in mass, get summoned in mass and get rezzed in mass?  Only 21 key components drop on the first island for example with a 4 hour respawn.  The sharing "exploit" gets around this inadequacy of drops and the linkdead problem with keys disappearing.  If keys are not to be shared, then make them last until you leave the zone like the components do, make them no drop and make more components drop (twice as many would be nice).<P>Why is the haste cap lower for bards than for other classes?  Bards are already reduced in the damage they can do by not having dual wield.  Having a lower haste cap compounds the problem.<BR>Example (numbers not exact):<BR>ranger: 10dmg/sec<BR>ranger w full haste (60%): 16 dmg/sec<BR>bard: 6dmg/sec<BR>bard w full haste (33%): 8 dmg/sec<BR>difference unhasted:ranger is 10/6 = 1.667 times better<BR>difference hasted: ranger is 16/8 = 2 times better<P>thats all.<BR>Celandro WhineSong
